# api-routes.js — Declarative API Route Map

## Purpose
Centralized HTTP route handlers extracted from web-server.js.
Follows the CIT `cmdMap` pattern: `{ 'METHOD /path': handler }`.

## Exports
- `createRoutes(ctx)` → builds route map with proxyManager/projectRoot closure
- `dispatch(routes, req, res)` → one-liner dispatch, returns boolean

## Routes (14 total)
| Key | Handler |
|-----|---------|
| `GET /api/instances` | List running MCP servers |
| `GET /api/project-info` | Portal metadata (name, path, pid) |
| `GET /api/server-status` | Uptime, agent count, monitor count |
| `GET /api/marketplace` | Installed servers + mock registry |
| `GET /api/adapter/status` | Adapter pool status |
| `GET /api/adapter/types` | Available adapter types |
| `POST /api/stop` | Graceful shutdown (exit 0) |
| `POST /api/restart` | Config-change restart (exit 2) |
| `POST /api/mcp-call` | Proxy MCP call to child server |
| `POST /api/marketplace/install` | Add server + restart |
| `POST /api/marketplace/remove` | Remove server + restart |
| `POST /api/lint-file` | ESLint server-side linting |
| `POST /api/adapter/run` | Execute prompt via adapter pool |

## Internal
- `parseBody(req, maxBytes)` — JSON body parser with size limit
- `MOCK_REGISTRY` — hardcoded available servers (future: registry API)
